                            <comment id="13575046" author="billgraham" created="Sat, 9 Feb 2013 02:13:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13577333" author="billgraham" created="Wed, 13 Feb 2013 04:56:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, a few comments:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Searching around it&apos;s not easy to find the Bigtop Pig rpm/deb packages. If we remove these artifacts from Pig we should update the Pig docs to direct people to Bigtop. Is this where people should be directed? &lt;a href=&quot;http://bigtop01.cloudera.org:8080/view/Bigtop-trunk/job/Bigtop-trunk-Pig/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://bigtop01.cloudera.org:8080/view/Bigtop-trunk/job/Bigtop-trunk-Pig/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There are also a number of deb/rpm support files below &lt;tt&gt;src/packages&lt;/tt&gt; that we should probably move as well if we discontinue support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13579482" author="alangates" created="Fri, 15 Feb 2013 20:25:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good catch, I&apos;ll deal with the now unnecessary files and upload a new patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13579588" author="alangates" created="Fri, 15 Feb 2013 23:17:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A new version of the patch that removes the files for rpm and deb under src/packages&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13579643" author="billgraham" created="Sat, 16 Feb 2013 00:50:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll take a look at the patch, but what are your thoughts on documentation or more generally, how we should point people to Bigtop for distros?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13582537" author="alangates" created="Wed, 20 Feb 2013 21:28:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How to get the bigtop artifacts looks like it&apos;s covered at &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/BIGTOP/How+to+install+Hadoop+distribution+from+Bigtop+0.5.0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/BIGTOP/How+to+install+Hadoop+distribution+from+Bigtop+0.5.0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue we&apos;ll face is that for a given release of Pig, it won&apos;t be picked up until after it&apos;s released.  So once Pig 0.11 is in Bigtop 0.6 and there&apos;s a similar page (I assume) we can go put in a link in our docs to point to it.  Maybe we should put links on our releases page pointing to the Bigtop docs on how to get rpms and debs for that release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13583301" author="billgraham" created="Thu, 21 Feb 2013 15:54:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 to patch and doc approach. A link from the releases page makes sense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13584927" author="alangates" created="Sat, 23 Feb 2013 01:25:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch checked into trunk.  I also checked in a change to the releases page to add information on getting Pig rpms and debs from Bigtop and getting stuff from maven.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
